        QFile/QTextStream â€“ file I/O
        QProcess â€“ external command execution

 âœ… Dependencies
        C++17 or later
        Qt Core 5 
        CMake (3.16+)

This installs Qt Core and other non-GUI essentials on Ubuntu 18.04 :

    sudo apt install qtbase5-dev
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Qt Core includes core non-GUI functionality: event loop, string handling, object model, timers, file system access, etc.

Qt Multimedia is a separate Qt module used for:
       Audio and video playback
       Recording
       Camera support
       Media device handling

To use Qt5::Multimedia, you must install it explicitly:

$sudo apt install qtmultimedia5-dev
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Use aqtinstall (No Qt Installer Needed)
You can install Qt 5.15.2 without the official installer using aqtinstall â€” a Python-based tool.

Steps:
Install Python and pip (if not already):

sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip

Install aqtinstall:
pip3 install aqtinstall

Download Qt 5.15.2 for Linux Desktop GCC:
aqt install-qt linux desktop 5.15.2 gcc_64 -O ~/Qt

Set Up Qt Creator:
Go to: Tools â†’ Options â†’ Qt Versions â†’ Add
Point to:
~/Qt/5.15.2/gcc_64/bin/qmake

Run your QML app:
~/Qt/5.15.2/gcc_64/bin/qmlscene main.qml

